Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over half the @Indonesian style spice mix{2%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%milliliter}(for the rice) into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pot{} from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

In a #large saucepan{}, combine the @peanut butter{30%grams}, @sambal paste{15%grams}, @ketjap manis{25%grams}, @hot water{2%tbsp} and the remaining Indonesian style spice mix.

Mix well until smooth.

> TIP: If your peanut butter has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Pop the #saucepan{} on medium-high heat and gradually whisk in the @coconut milk{180%milliliter}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%milliliter}(for the sauce), then bring to the boil.

Simmer, stirring constantly, until thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat, then stir in half the lime juice and season with salt.

Once the sweet potato is cooked, pop the #satay pan{} back on medium heat and stir in the sweet potato.

Add the @peas{120%grams} to the pan and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with more salt and lime juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, stir through the lime zest then share out between your serving bowls.

Spoon the satay curry over the zesty rice and finish with a sprinkling of peanuts.

Serve any remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over. Enjoy!